-- Stocks Hit 1-Month High on Strong Factory Reports
-- Nick Baker
-- 2010-06-15T20:02:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-15/s-p-500-erases-decline-for-year-oil-gains-on-new-york-manufacturing-data.html

          
          
             Stocks rallied, sending the Standard
& Poor’s 500 Index to the highest level since May 18, and oil
climbed as growth in New York manufacturing added to signs the
global economy is weathering Europe’s debt crisis. Greek bonds
sank after Moody’s Investors Service cut the nation’s credit
rating to junk.  
 The S&P 500 climbed 2.3 percent to 1,115.16 as of
preliminary closing data at 4 p.m. in New York after the Federal
Reserve Bank of New York’s general economic index showed an 11th
consecutive month of growth. Oil rallied above $77 a barrel and
the Reuters/Jefferies CRB Index of commodities posted a seventh
straight gain, the longest stretech of gains since March 2007.
The euro strengthened above $1.23. Greek 10-year bond yields
jumped 74 basis points to 9.08 percent.  
 The S&P 500 erased its 2010 decline.  
          
          


  


        